//Paraspinal mass - I know - Characterization I

Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 08 of Spine MRI

When I select 'Finding' radio button
And I select 'Paraspinal mass' from Finding dropdown menu
And I select 'I know' radio button
And I select 'Characterization I' tab

Then 'Localization z-axis, reference to vertebra' localizer is enabled
And 'Max. axial diameter' input field is enabled
And 'Expansion in z-axis' input field is enabled

And 'Localization axial' localizer is enabled

And 'Differential diagnosis 1' dropdown menu is enabled
And 'T1w signal' slide bar is enabled
And 'T2w signal' slide bar is enabled

And 'Hypointense after fat saturation' checkbox is enabled
And 'Isointense to cerebrospinal fluid' checkbox is enabled


And 'Homogeneous' radio button is enabled
And 'Heterogeneous' radio button is enabled

And 'Mirror formation' checkbox is enabled
And 'Calcification' checkbox is enabled
And 'Capsule/membrane' checkbox is enabled
